Interface MessageQueue

All Known Implementing Classes:
BoundedDequeBasedMailbox.MessageQueue, BoundedMailbox.MessageQueue, BoundedPriorityMailbox.MessageQueue, DurableMessageQueue, DurableMessageQueueWithSerialization, FileBasedMessageQueue, NodeMessageQueue, PeekMailbox, UnboundedDequeBasedMailbox.MessageQueue, UnboundedMailbox.MessageQueue, UnboundedPriorityMailbox.MessageQueue
public interface MessageQueue

A MessageQueue is one of the core components in forming an Akka Mailbox. The MessageQueue is where the normal messages that are sent to Actors will be enqueued (and subsequently dequeued) It needs to at least support N producers and 1 consumer thread-safely.

cleanUp

void cleanUp(ActorRef owner,
             MessageQueue deadLetters)
Called when the mailbox this queue belongs to is disposed of. Normally it is expected to transfer all remaining messages into the dead letter queue which is passed in. The owner of this MessageQueue is passed in if available (e.g. for creating DeadLetters()), &ldquo;/deadletters&rdquo; otherwise.
